%section#places
  .container
    .divider
    .content
      .row-fluid
        .span12
          %h1 Places to visit
      .row-fluid
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('national-cowboy-museum.png')
          .flip-on
            The National Cowboy & Western Heritage Museum is America’s premier institution of Western history, art and culture. Founded in 1955, the museum in Oklahoma City collects, preserves and exhibits an internationally renowned collection of Western art and artifacts while sponsoring dynamic educational programs and ground-breaking scholarly research to stimulate interest in the enduring legacy of our American West. More than 10 million visitors from around the world have sought out this unique museum to gain better understanding of the West: a region and a history that permeates our national culture.
            %br
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.nationalcowboymuseum.org/'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('OK-national-memorial-museum.png')
          .flip-on
            The Outdoor Symbolic Memorial, spanning the downtown block where the April 19, 1995, terror bombing occurred, has been widely recognized as perhaps the most hopeful and unique memorial site in the United States. From a peaceful field of lighted chairs, across a shallow Reflecting Pool to the sturdy Survivor Tree, the Memorial’s outdoor sections create a sense of calm assurance.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.oklahomacitynationalmemorial.org/'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('penn-square-mall.png')
          .flip-on
            Penn Square Mall is Oklahoma City's premiere fashion destination because of its excellent mix of over 140 specialty shops, and comfortable climate controlled atmosphere. Centrally located in the heart of Oklahoma City's popular Business and Tourism District, Penn Square offers the latest from women's fashion and sporting goods to dining options that include JCPenney, Dillard's, Macy's, Apple, Michael Kors, LUSH Cosmetics, Oakley, Cheesecake Factory and Elephant Bar Restaurant. Conveniently located with easy access off of Interstate-44 at the intersection of Pennsylvania and Northwest Expressway.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.simon.com/Mall/?id=811'
      .row-fluid.grid-picture
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('myriad-botanical-gardens.png')
          .flip-on
            The Myriad Botanical Gardens is one of Oklahoma City’s most beloved public spaces, offering its visitors a 17 acre natural escape in the very heart of the metro known as downtown Oklahoma City.
            %br
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.myriadgardens.org/'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('bricktown.png')
          .flip-on
            Bricktown, a once abandoned old warehouse district, received a much needed facelift with the passing of MAPS (Metropolitan Area Projects) in 1993 when Oklahoma City took on a massive public facility enhancement project. Now a vital part of the city, Bricktown is a much sought after destination for locals and tourists alike. The breathtaking canal lends itself to the picturesque look and a great variety of unique and exquisite restaurants, retailers and entertainment venues.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.bricktownokc.com/'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('chicksaw-cultural-center.png')
          .flip-on
            The Chickasaw Cultural Center is located in Sulphur, Oklahoma near the Chickasaw National Recreation Area. Its 109-acre campus is home to historical museums with interactive exhibits on Chickasaw tribal history, traditional dancing, and Chickasaw language. Visitors can explore a traditional tribal village and a garden honoring members of the Chickasaw Nation Hall of Fame.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.chickasawculturalcenter.com/'
      .row-fluid.grid-picture
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('sonic.png')
          .flip-on
            Sonic was first opened in the 1950's in Patricia's hometown, Shawnee, OK. There are currently over 200 Sonics in Oklahoma.
            %br
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.sonicdrivein.com/business/profile/backgrounder.jsp'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('braums.png')
          .flip-on
            Braum’s Ice Cream and Dairy Stores…just the name conjures up visions of scrumptious ice cream, giant hamburgers, dairy fresh milk, fresh baked goods, even meats, fruits and vegetables.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.braums.com/'
        .span4.flip
          .flip-off
            =image_tag image_path('cattlemens-steakhouse.png')
          .flip-on
            Cattlemen's Cafe opened its doors to hungry cowboys, ranchers, cattle haulers and the like in 1910. Since 1945, Cattlemen's Steakhouse has become a gathering place for all kinds of folks. Check the walls of the dining rooms and view the drawings of all the well-knowns who have sampled Cattlemen's fare.
            = link_to 'Visit Site &raquo;'.html_safe, 'http://www.cattlemensrestaurant.com/history'
